text.name: Erika Senft Miller
text.text:
Scene Two: Falling

Tears dripping
catching
gripping
tears slipping through
falling
falling into long bottomless seas
falling into love
tears falling into love

text.name: Erika Senft Miller
text.text:
Scene One: Slumping

Seemingly still on the outside,
Cellular and fluids — lots of movement —
continuously pumping, flowing, rippling within the tree
In tree time rhythm.
Photosynthesis - a mutual exchange
Give and take
In tree time rhythm
Tapping sweet sap in spring - boiling down to maple syrup
Fueling us
Us fueling the tree
In tree time rhythm.
Partially blind, it's best this way.
I see in an attempt to see more.
Apparently, my right thigh. It's locked solid.
what is listening without registering and understanding?
At the end of all the light.
through the loss of self in a state of flowing through the moments
where i'm needed and where i want
At the end of your wanting gaze.
part of being creative is approaching a new idea from a new perspective, ego can get in the way of that
a pretty pretty net of knots
when i'm angry, when i don't have a choice
with my eyes and my fingers
by imagining a destination or finding one
lots of places and no where at all
laying ego aside for the sake of the mission
on the FBI's most wanted list
when I look in her eyes
when things get tough and I am hungry
sweetly in my own way, always with laughter
my desire for challenge, growth, and exploration
through reliance on a mechanism hundreds of millions of years in the making that cannot be trusted to ignore only the irrelevant
when I do the hokey pokey
when others share thoughts and feelings
I'm in it for the money
the world coming together in a cornucopia of love and joy
Yes, because art is a reflection of oneself made public. We are our egos.
to fear. to challenge. to new things.
that sounds like a corporate question
By seeing what around me is solid and not moving that way.
I fall when I am all about me.
I forget to lean in until I'm asked.
I show up on the edges.
My families of origin and of marriage.
Collaboration -- saying things out loud. Interacting with public services.
The dizzy happiness of moments past.
when my nose wants to smell closer
No. I think ego inhibits creative expression
By the act of trying to remove ego from the expression.
connecting with others at a meaningful level
I watch for the quieter parts of people
that depends on the intent of the ego, in some instances yes, in some, no
time to process what i hear
Off the edge of the knife
by doing what feels out of my comfort zone
where no egos tread...anything is possible
when i need to stretch boundaries
when i am looking at bugs
trees, the wind, phone calls with loved ones
undo all the bad things that politicians have done to me and my family
Snakeskin boots ya gaggle o' loud geese
often i choose not to move
i let the movement choose me
